Shifting our attention from the external to the internal is foundational to building self-awareness and doing the inner-work. 

We can learn a lot about ourselves and where we are being asked to grow when we practice self-inquiry.

As always, many of these questions are nuanced and the whole picture cannot be fit into a tiny caption.

Notice how you feel in your body with each question that’s relevant to you and pause to really be with it. You may choose to take some of these questions and journal them to go deeper.

🌿 @sheleanaaiyana

All relationships have their challenges - so please note that in this series I’m not talking about variations of normal ups and downs.

I'm specifically speaking to roller-coaster relationships that are often built entirely off of trauma-bonding and involve a lot of game playing, chaos, manipulation and unsafe or extremely insecure dynamics where there’s really nothing other than two people projecting their pain at one another.

When we feel unbearable passion or intensity toward another person and convince ourselves that we have to ride it out because they are our soul mate, we’re really just hanging on to a false narrative that allows us to ride the temporary high but keeps us chained in a painful and limiting spot.

In honor of @jessicaaustinchildbirth and in prayer for her husband and daughter. The center flowers represent Jess (large deep red) the bright orange and pink represent her husband and the small light pink flower represent her daughter - all being held in circle by spirit, community, and family. Around the circle are 10 stones to represent 10 moons, Jessica's dharma path as a birth worker and profound teacher. All around them are more flowers, representing her friends and family, and then all of the pinecones enclosing the circle, sealed with dried rose petals represent her extended community, students, and clients - everyone impacted by her work who is holding her in their hearts forever. The ferns in all four directions weave us all together, hugged by the strength and protection of cedar - a symbol of the courage it takes to open our hearts and allow for grief to move through us. 🌊

This life is a precious one. It was a true gift to be in your presence Jessica, and to witness such devotion in another being. You have left this world better than you found it, and I have no doubt that your soul work continues on now.

node.text:
There are many valid reasons for a relationship ending. Sometimes it’s not possible to transform the current partnership into something new because the entire foundation is cracked or was never there to begin with. Breakups are medicine too.

But there are also times where we are being called to lean in and let the partnership shape us, strip us of our illusions and rebirth us time and time again.

A Conscious Partnership doesn’t hold the other to a fixed reality, it makes space for each partner to die and rebirth a thousand times. Each time, coming back with more authenticity, more awareness, more vulnerability and truth.

Allowing our partners to change and celebrating their growth is the only way to keep energy and passion alive.

When we hold back our truth or hold on too tight to who we think a person is, we close the door on magic.

But when we remain open, express our desires, embody the energy we yearn for in our partnership and praise each other for the little and monumental shifts that occur over the years - the relationship only gets better with time.

Questions or thoughts?

🌿 @sheleanaaiyana

All of the less than/better than projections need to be put to bed before we can truly embody the work.

Anyone who enters the space as a teacher or leader in any way will have to watch our for the distortion and inflated sense of self-importance that can come along with getting a lot of attention or having a big following count.

Similarly, we also have to watch out for the “I’m not good enough” story if we don’t have one. Some of the most gifted healers I’ve met have no social media following at all - who cares!

When we claim our gifts and step into service from truth, it’s not about celebrity status or being seen. It’s about heart connection. It’s about impact and dharma.

No one is above or below any of us. The quality of our hearts isn’t rooted in whether we are externally validated or recognized - it’s expressed in how we show up for ourselves, our families and those who surround us.

🌿 @sheleanaaiyana

node.text:
This is the second of two Full Moons we have in the sign of the Sacred Rebel this month. The first Full Moon, which occurred on July 23rd, culminated in the early degrees of Aquarius, inviting us to break free of the attachments that have been dimming our light.

Now, this Full Moon culminates at the last degree of Aquarius, inviting us to awaken to the full splendor of that light. You can think of these two Full Moons as the book ends of Leo season, taking us on a journey to rediscover our brilliance, our radiance, and the power of our authenticity.

The sign of Aquarius, represents your inner Sacred Rebel, the part of you who dares to break free of the status quo in the name of universal progress and revolution… because, sometimes, honoring the collective light means walking the road less travelled, in order to pave the new trails that awaken us all.

What differentiates this Full Moon is its close proximity to Jupiter retrograde in Aquarius, and the fact that it occurs at the 29th degree – just before the Moon enters Pisces, and just before the Sun enters Virgo. The 29th degree of any sign marks the place of ending and transition, where we are asked to decide what we are taking with us on the next stages of our journey. We are being asked to mine for the gold of Leo season that we wish to take forward with us into Virgo season. Leo season helps us find our courage and leads us to the joy of shining our light; while Virgo season teaches us to offer up that joy in service to ourselves and others.

These themes are amplified with this Moon’s proximity to Jupiter Retrograde in Aquarius. Jupiter is the planet of expansion, growth, integration, and higher learning, and is reminding us that we have all learned something over the last month.

Perhaps something especially important about ourselves, potentially related to a resurrected hope or the potential of a dream fulfilled.

Don’t underestimate that “something” that you have learned. It is the spark that wants to awaken you to the next version of you.

node.text:
Those of us who had to be the parent when we were really the child often have a hard time receiving. 

I know this pattern well - I’m wired to do it all myself, to be strong, to push through, to take care of. But to slow down, receive, and let myself fall apart? That’s my edge.

Our history shapes us into the people we are today, but our awareness and clarity is what allows us to grow, stretch and move out of the roles we were put in when we were young.

If we hold ourselves to one static mode of being: survivor mode, strong one mode, the I’ve got it all together mode, we miss out on the full spectrum of beauty life has for us when we lean into what feels new and possibly even scary for us.

If you had to the parent when you were really the child, chances are you never really got to experience what it was like to be surrendered, taken care of or provided for.

Sometimes I still find myself in shock when my husband describes his teenage years and tells me that his parents were helping him pay for something or setting boundaries because by the time I was 16 I was out on my own, working two jobs and home-schooling myself.

If we were never given the opportunity to be a child, our nervous systems might feel the safest when we’re in full control. But full control doesn’t always lead to happiness, because control in itself is an illusion.

No matter where you’ve come from, you are an innocent being and you deserve to receive. You aren’t responsible for taking care of everyone else at the expense of your health or sanity. It’s ok to let go, it’s ok to rest, it’s ok to cry, it’s ok to not know.

Open yourself to the deeper layers of healing that want to come through when you surrender control and trust that life is preparing you for great love.

node.text:
The nuclear family structure is really only one way to experience relationship.

There are as many possible relationship dynamics as there are humans. Our cultural conditioning has convinced many of us that relationship “should” look a certain way, and for many of us, it’s one of the main reasons we’re blocked in love.

Relationship can be a co-creative process. You get to negotiate the terms and how the partnership nourishes you and your partner(s) in all of the ways that make you unique.

While it’s common to fall into relationship, the other option is to build consciously from the ground up, with a bit of a road map, a clear idea of your values, and the awareness of what you all want to give, receive and experience in the container you’re creating together.

Your relationship doesn’t need to (and never will) look like anyone else’s relationship. Any couples you may pedestal on social media or elsewhere are not you, it’s wonderful to celebrate others and their love, but your relationship is about you and the other(s) you’re with - let it be an expression of your essence.

Some of the things that make sense for other couples might feel wrong for you when you check in with your own body. Some of the ways other couples feel energized and lit up, might not be the correct path for you.

We cannot model an external relationship dynamic as our own without being anchored in our own truth and awareness. Once we know who we are and what we stand for, we can claim it in our relationships.

🌿 @sheleanaaiyana
